        <h2>High-Resolution Satellite Imagery Analysis</h2>
        <p>GeoPACHA-AI leverages high-resolution multispectral satellite imagery from WorldView-2 and WorldView-3 to analyze vast areas of the Andes. Our Vision Transformer models process this imagery to detect patterns relevant to archaeological research, enabling insights that were previously unattainable through traditional ground-based survey methods alone.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose fade-in">
        <h2>Innovative AI Techniques</h2>
        <p>Utilizing cutting-edge AI models like DeepAndes, we analyze vast areas of the Andes, providing unprecedented insights into historical human adaptation and settlement networks. Our approach combines self-supervised learning with expert-curated training data to achieve high accuracy in archaeological feature detection across diverse Andean landscapes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose fade-in">
        <h2>Collaborative Efforts</h2>
        <p>Our platform brings together archaeologists and machine learning experts from institutions across the Americas, fostering collaboration to enhance research outcomes and drive innovation in the field. Regional editors and their survey teams contribute deep local knowledge that guides and validates the AI detections, creating a virtuous cycle of improving model performance.</p>
      </div>
